snippet.textDisplay:
Terminator should be a franchise, it just shouldn't be THAT franchise. A franchise based around a future war with an AI that involves time travel... what's not to like? But to be a franchise it needs to escape from two things 1) Arnold Schwarzenegger and 2) Terminator 2. The TV series and Salvation both demonstrated that potential. Both had flaws (more Salvation than TSCC) but they were very different from each other and neither tried to be Terminator 2. All the other entries tried to be T2 part 2. That is bollocks.

The people calling it nothing but a vehicle for Arnold need to go back and really give The Terminator another viewing. There is SO much potential there and it's a far more cerebral and tense film than T2. Terminator 2 is still one of the best action movies ever made, but it was also one of the most expensive and it's insane to keep trying to repeat that when you have so many other options.

I actually came up with a great idea for a trilogy myself, didn't take long and even though I'm no script writer I know for a fact it was better than any of the ideas in any of these movies since T2.
